<BR><BR>

<A NAME="1"><H3>Task 1</H3></A>

<P>

Compile all of the class files for the server.

<p>
<HR WIDTH="80%">

<P>
In a separate DOS console, go to the Server subdirectory for this exercise.
Compile all of the java files with the command:
<p>
<CODE>javac *.java</CODE>
<P>
This will compile the server and all of the client classes that will be
bootstrap loaded across the network.
<p>
<A NAME="2"><H3>Task 2</H3></A>

<P>

Create the <CODE>stub</CODE> and <CODE>skeleton</CODE> files for the remote object implementation.

<p>
<HR WIDTH="80%">

<P>

Use the <CODE>rmic</CODE> utility on the implementation class, <CODE>RemoteModelMgrImpl</CODE>
and the <CODE>RemoteModelImpl</CODE> class.
<CODE>rmic RemoteModelMgrImpl
rmic RemoteModelImpl</CODE>

<p>
<A NAME="3"><H3>Task 3</H3></A>

<P>

Run the RMI server program.

<p>
<HR WIDTH="80%">

<P>

Use the <CODE>java</CODE> program to run the server
<CODE>java LocalRemoteServer</CODE>


